===Etymology 2===
From ''hail'', a variant of [[hale]] ‘health, safety’.

====Verb====
{{en-verb}}

# {{transitive}} To [[greet]].
#: ''Hail Caesar''
# {{transitive}} To [[praise]] enthusiastically.
#: ''He was hailed as a hero.''
# {{transitive}} To call out to loudly in order to gain the attention of.
#: ''Hail a taxi''
# be a native of 
#: ''She hails from Kalamazoo''


